## Traps

- kaizen tests per-package: `cd packages/<pkg> && ../../.venv/bin/python -m pytest ...`.
  A COMBINED cross-package pytest over kaizen-agents + kailash-kaizen hits
  `ImportPathMismatchError` (both ship `tests/conftest.py`) — rootdir artifact,
  NOT a defect; CI runs each package in its own working-directory.
- pre-commit shim stale interpreter → invoke via `.venv/bin/python -m pre_commit run --files <files>`.
  isort/ruff/black auto-fix (report "Failed" on modify) → re-stage + re-run to idempotency.
- `python-use-type-annotations` pygrep hook matches the literal `# type` comment
  fragment — reword comments to avoid `# type` (git.md).
- pyright resolves `kaizen.*` against the installed wheel (stale) → false
  "unknown import symbol"; pytest via editable `.venv` is authoritative.
- Autonomy examples must compile on Python 3.11 (no f-string-backslash; 3.12+ only).
- uv index-cache lag on fresh PyPI publish → `uv pip install --refresh`, else
  pip `--no-cache-dir` fallback (build-repo-release-discipline Rule 2).
- Release tag convention: `kaizen-v<X.Y.Z>` triggers `publish-pypi.yml`.
